cs|4|ht|k|at| {Historical note:} |cs|2|at|{^FThe Gerber convention was developed in 1938 by John
^FGerber of Houston. Gerber saw how effectively Blackwood worked
^Fand sought to extend the same principle to notrump sequences without
^Fgiving up the quantitative raise to 4NT. Thus, Gerber's 4@C Ace-ask
^Fwas born. The Gerber convention is especially brilliant as there is no
